{"cursor":"9159","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"__NOTOC__ {{Infobox Bridge |bridge_name = Qatar Bahrain Bridge |image =\n|image_size = 250px |caption = |official_name = |also_known_as = Qatar Bahrain\nFriendship Bridge |carries = Motor vehicle and Rail |crosses = Gulf of Bahrain\n|locale = and |maint = Qatar and Bahrain Causeway Foundation |id = |design =\n|mainspan = |length = |width = |clearance= |below = |traffic = |open = 2022\n(planned) |closed = |toll = |map_cue = |map_image= |map_text = |map_width=\n|coordinates = |lat = |long = }}\n\nThe 'Qatar Bahrain Causeway' (also referred to as the 'Qatar Bahrain Friendship\nBridge') is an often announced, often delayed planned causeway between the two\nArab states of Qatar and Bahrain. It was announced on 13 December 2008 that\nconstruction would start in early 2009, [http://www.menafn.com/menafn/1093224108/Work-on-QatarBahrain-\ncauseway-to-start-next-month \"Work on Qatar-Bahrain causeway to start next\nmonth\"] and would cost approximately US$2.3 billion to complete. As of\nJune 2010, construction had not started, and the Qatar-Bahrain Causeway project\nwas on hold, while the contracting consortium involved with the project was said\nto be demobilising, according to a source at the Qatar Bahrain Causeway\nFoundation (QBCF). [http://www.indisteel.com/news_article/qatar-bahrain-causeway-usd4-\nbln-project-hold-says-qatar-bahrain-causeway-foundation \"Qatar-Bahrain Causeway\nUSD4 bln project on hold - says Qatar Bahrain Causeway Foundation\"] On 14\nJanuary 2011, Bahrain's Foreign Minister stated that the project should\nnevertheless be considered as a must for both countries: \"This is one economic\nmarket, one economic zone that should be well-connected, and the bridge is an\nintegral part of that\". [http://www.meed.com/sectors/construction/qatar-bahrain-causeway-\nstill-planned/3098794.article \"Qatar-Bahrain Causeway still planned - MEED.com -\n24 May 2011\"] [http://www.gulf-daily-\nnews.com/NewsDetails.aspx?storyid=296132 \"GREEN LIGHT\"] On 27 April 2011,\nan announcement was made, quoting an anonymous source of Bahrain's Al Wasat\nnewspaper, that construction of the causeway would start in 2011 for completion\nin 2015, at the cost of approximately $5 billion. [http://www.thepeninsulaqatar.com/qatar/150343-qatar-bahrain-\ncauseway-to-be-ready-by-2015.html \"Qatar-Bahrain causeway to be ready by\n2015\"] By December 2012, Bahrain's Foreign Minister was invoking financial\nturbulence to say that the bridge construction would only be completed by \"a\nlittle before the 2022 FIFA World Cup.\" [http://thepeninsulaqatar.com/qatar/219002-qatar-bahrain-causeway-faces-\ndelay-says-minister.html \"Qatar-Bahrain causeway faces delay, says\nminister\"]\n","linknr":198,"url":"Qatar–Bahrain_Friendship_Bridge","recorded":1375082897,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Qatar_Bahrain_Causeway&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Qatar_Bahrain_Causeway&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Qatar_Bahrain_Causeway","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Qatar%E2%80%93Bahrain_Friendship_Bridge&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Motor_vehicle","/wiki/Rail_transport","/wiki/Gulf_of_Bahrain","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Flag